	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f96817930121937><tr><td id=headerrow><span id=sj>RE: Thought for Magi around 30</span></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=887><span id=Sage>Zuranthium</span></a>, <span id=Sage>Sage</span><br><span id=notbold>390 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Sep 5th 2:41 PM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[4.56]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>&nbsp;&nbsp; The only problem I find with dungeons is that by them time you get to the dungeon and form a group(which can drain a lot of time), you could have been soloing and making a lot of exp. The other thing I find is that it is hard to find players that REALLY know how to play their class. So in a dungeon, you will likely be stuck with some people that will not do things for the best of the group and cause trains, pull while the group is hurt, not assist the people that need to be assisted, break mezzes, etc. Until the mid 30's, when soloing exp. starts to slow down for the 'soloing classes', it is my general opinion that you would be much better off soloing. I would say that 95% of the time you wouldn't be able to find a dungeon group that would give more exp. or better loot(since you have to slpit it between multiple people), then if you were to solo.<br>  This is only dungeon groups though. Outdoor groups that want to take multiple spawns or camps can definately give you better exp. than soloing. However, in deungeons there is a lot more risk and it is a lot easier for people to mess up, hence you will die and your exp. gain will be cut down significantly.<br>  However, once you get to higher levels you won't have as much problems. If the person was good enough to get to level 40 then they probably know how to play their class. There will be less fools becuase the players will be much more expirienced. Also, I would have to say that you DEFINATELY want to get into groups in the mid 40's. IMO, that is when soloing exp. becomes horrible and dungeon/outdoor group play becomes necessary. I am not saying the soloing classes can't solo at those levels, I am just saying it is a lot harder. At level 10 a magician could take a low red con. At level 50 a magician would be hard-pressed to do a white. Plus there is a lot more downtime at higher levels if soloing.<br><br>Good post Adiemus, i definately agree with your point on using air pets against casters (heck, in a dungeon an air pet would all-around be the best choice anyway...hehe they are my favorite too).<br><br>Zuranthium/Corpusnuntia/Divineshadow/Naltec/Natalos/Sunsong/Plantmaster<br><br>Player of many characters on the Nameless server.<br><br>P.S. - If you haven't read the Harry Potter books I suggest you do. It has nothing to do with this topic, but I had to tell you. Many people won't read them becuase they think they are childish. However, after reading the series I can definately say you need to read them. Even if your an adult; many of my former teachers have read them and loved them.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
