	   <tr><td colspan=2>If you plan on grouping at higher levels, you must group at lower levels.&nbsp;&nbsp;At the high levels, you are known by your reputation.  My guild has lists of those who are exceptionally good at their roles, and those who cause death.  Mages can be a very viable grouping class if you know what you are doing.  I'd do soloing when I don't have the time to invest in finding and staying in a group.<br>&nbsp;<br>34th Mage of Cazic-Thule<br>Member of The Chosen Elite<br>25th Druid of The Nameless<br></td></tr>
