	   <tr><td colspan=2>Thanks for the kind words Zuranthium...muchly appreciated.<br><br>I guess I am just a social animal- I prefer grouping to soloing, with the reservation here that I group with intellegent players who know their roles. This is especially true in places like Unrest and Mistmoor., but a general rule anywhere. If I want to die, I can certainly arrange to do that thru my own stupidity, rather than rely on that of others, y'know?<br><br>The relative merits of soloing vs. grouping have been debated at great length, and I think you'd be hard-pressed to change anyone's mind whatever you say. I take the stance that, grouped, you can take on many more mobs with less downtime PROVIDED all folks work together and don't waste mana/hit points. Yes, xp is divided among however many in the group, but if you can take on 6 mobs in the same time that you could take one solo (assuming here that the spawns can support such), the xp is roughly equal and the loot probably as good or possibly even a bit better.<br><br>Of course, if you happen to be unfortunate enough to group with a bunch of morons, then all the above obviously does not apply...<br><br>I will concede the point you raised about time wasted looking for groups that you could spend soloing. many is the time that I have camped a character in sheer frustration after spending half an hour shouting LFG! LFG! to no avail. In times like that, thank goodness I have a druid or magician to fall back on to solo a bit so I can do something constructive.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
